				\begin{document}$$\sigma_{pcm} S_{p,pcm} \frac{\partial T}{{\partial \tau }} = \nabla \cdot \left( {K\nabla T} \right)$$\end{document}where σ is the density and the subscripts pcm indicates the properties for PCM, K is the thermal conductivity, and T is the temperature.

