Similar type of numerical study was carried by Ye et al. [141] to optimize the temperature distribution, maximum temperature in LiFePO4 battery cell and pressure distribution in mini channel cooling plates in which the water is used as a coolant. The mini channel cooling plates were installed on top and bottom parts of the battery cells which are arranged in series connection. The orthogonal experimental design strategy was used to obtain the optimal configuration and battery module parameters and surrogate model was used to catch the optimal geometry of cooling plates. Further the 3D thermal battery model was built by using CATIA CAD package and analysis was done by using Ansys Fluent software. The output of this study shows that by increasing the number of channels and cross section of cooling plates the temperature distribution and pressure drop can be reduced to greater extent by keeping flowrate of water constant at the channel inlet. The temperature rise in the battery module was verified theoretically and numerically by using following equation-35ΔTc=Mα2fiSp\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
